Police arrived at the scene and rescued one of the suspects. [Kennedy Gachuhi, Standard]  Two suspected phone-snatchers were on Thursday burnt in Nakuru Town, with one of the victims succumbing to his burn injuries at the scene.  The other suspect was taken to hospital in critical condition, police said.  Nakuru East Sub-County Police Commander Elena Kabukuru told The Standard that the male suspects, who were aboard a motorbike, attempted to snatch a phone from a pedestrian, leading to their pursuit by, among others, boda boda operators.  The suspects were cornered at the Geoffrey Kamau Avenue, doused in petrol and set alight.  Two killed in Migaa road accident  Nakuru joins Unesco’s list of creative cities  Nakuru police launch hunt for female suspect, seize spent cartridges  Two key witnesses in Nakuru German’s succession case dead, court hears Police arrived at the scene, and rescued one of the suspects, who hadn’t lost his life at the time.  The deceased was taken to a Nakuru hospital morgue.   Serikali ya kaunti ya Nakuru yatoa pendekezo la kuzuia uvuvi katika ziwa Naivasha  KENHA urges Kenyans plying the Nairobi-Nakuru highway to use alternative routes  Tussle over the ownership of land in Ngongogeri, Nakuru threatening peace amongst disputing parties By James Munyeki | 2 hours ago By Irissheel Shanzu | 3 hours ago By Nikko Tanui | 3 hours ago By Lynn Kolongei | 4 hours ago